iption type="plain">Sen. Elizabeth Warren, D-Mass., questioned Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth about traders appearing to benefit from &#34;inside information&#34; about developments in the Iran war.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_04/1777569030702_f_mo_dc_warren_hegseth_trading_260430_S3_1920x1080-sv506w.jpg"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 17:10:38 GMT</pubDate><title>Warren questions Hegseth about insider trading around Iran war developments</title><updateDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 17:11:38 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Scott Wong</dc:creator><dc:creator>Melanie Zanona</dc:creator><dc:creator>Kyle Stewart</dc:creator><dc:contributor>Brennan Leach</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>Lizzie Jensen</dc:contributor><dateTimeWritten>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 16:30:16 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Congress voted to fund most of the Department of Homeland Security, ending a 75-day shutdown. ICE and the Border Patrol will be funded separately because of Democratic opposition.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/congress/congress-expected-end-record-75-day-partial-government-shutdown-rcna342903</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/congress/congress-expected-end-record-75-day-partial-government-shutdown-rcna342903</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260417-capitol-hill-ch-1528-1fd938.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Alex Wroblewski</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Capitol exterior.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Homeland Security Secretary Markwayne Mullin had warned lawmakers that if they didn&#39;t pass funding by Thursday, emergency funding would run out and thousands of workers wouldn&#39;t be paid.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260417-capitol-hill-ch-1528-1fd938.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 16:30:16 GMT</pubDate><title>Record-long Department of Homeland Security shutdown ends</title><updateDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 20:58:24 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Freddie Clayton</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 18:07:17 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>As King Charles III closed out his four-day state visit to the U.S. on Thursday, President Donald Trump issued a three-word assessment of the monarch.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/world/europe/king-charles-trump-set-return-mission-accomplished-rcna342865</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/world/europe/king-charles-trump-set-return-mission-accomplished-rcna342865</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260430-charles-trump-mb-1659-86a5b6.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Samir Hussein</media:credit><media:text type="plain">King Charles III And Queen Camilla Wrap Up State Visit In Washington DC Area</media:text><media:description type="plain">King Charles and President Trump during a farewell ceremony at the White House on April 30, 2026.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260430-charles-trump-mb-1700-864b00.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Samir Hussein</media:credit><media:text type="plain">King Charles III And Queen Camilla Wrap Up State Visit In Washington DC Area</media:text><media:description type="plain">Trump bids Charles farewell outside the White House on Thursday.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260428-king-charles-capitol-vsb-2115-91d765.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1666" width="2500"><media:credit>Henry Nicholls</media:credit><media:text type="plain">King Charles III in Washington D.C.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Charles addressed a joint meeting of Congress at the Capitol on Tuesday.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260430-charles-trump-mb-1701-f3285f.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1666" width="2500"><media:credit>Alex Brandon</media:credit><media:text type="plain">US Britain Royal Visit Trump</media:text><media:description type="plain">King Charles departs the South Lawn on Thursday.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260430-charles-trump-mb-1659-86a5b6.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 18:07:17 GMT</pubDate><title>King Charles set to return home with a quiet sense of mission accomplished</title><updateDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 18:58:51 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Saba Hamedy</dc:creator><dc:creator>Chloe Melas</dc:creator><dc:creator>Erick Mendoza</dc:creator><dc:contributor>Marlene Lenthang</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>Andrew Blankstein</dc:contributor><dateTimeWritten>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 21:02:08 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Pop star Britney Spears has been charged in Southern California with driving under the influence, the Ventura County District Attorney’s Office said.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/pop-culture/pop-culture-news/britney-spears-charged-dui-drugs-alcohol-southern-california-rcna342985</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/pop-culture/pop-culture-news/britney-spears-charged-dui-drugs-alcohol-southern-california-rcna342985</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upl